 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-W2-003: Guard partial_cmp().unwrap() on f64 in Cheeger/Fiedler computation against NaN. PROBLEM: query/graph.rs:2388 and 2427 call .partial_cmp(&fiedler_result.vector[b]).unwrap(). Fiedler vector values come from eigendecomposition of the graph Laplacian. If the coupling matrix is ill-conditioned (near-singular, or containing NaN from prior computation), eigenvalues may be NaN. partial_cmp returns None on NaN; unwrap() panics, crashing the topology compilation pipeline. SOLUTION: Replace .partial_cmp(...).unwrap() with .partial_cmp(...).unwrap_or(std::cmp::Ordering::Equal). Additionally, add NaN guard at the eigendecomposition output: if any eigenvalue is NaN, return a TopologyError::IllConditionedMatrix instead of proceeding. VERIFICATION: (1) Unit test: Fiedler computation on identity matrix (trivial) succeeds. (2) Unit test: Fiedler computation on matrix with NaN entry returns TopologyError, not panic. (3) proptest: no panic for any f64 coupling matrix values (including NaN, Inf, subnormal). DEPENDS-ON: None (leaf task). INTERACTS-WITH: W3-005 (topology performance, same code region)."
